HOUSE RESOLUTION 93
By Bulso
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Hudson Allain on
being named the 2024 WILLCO Awards Male
Track and Field Athlete of the Year.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to recognize and commend those successful high school
athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to Tennessee and serve as
exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Hudson Allain of Brentwood High School,
an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has proven himself to be a
formidable competitor in track and field; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of his success on the track, Hudson Allain was named Male
Track and Field Athlete of the Year at the 2024 WILLCO Awards celebration; and
WHEREAS, Hudson Allain led the Bruins to back-to-back State track and field
championships in 2023 and 2024; and
WHEREAS, in 2024, Hudson Allain won individual State championships in the 200-
meter and 400-meter sprints, and he anchored the State champion relay teams in the 4X200
meter and 4X400 meter events; and
WHEREAS, Hudson Allain epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as he
has achieved a high level of success in track and field while evincing great character; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Allain's notable achievements are a source of great pride for his family,
his community, and his school, and it is appropriate that we recognize this accomplished
athlete; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and
